# `golem` (runtime)

**Game loop + integrated networking + world data + interest management:** `Server`, `ServerConfig` (with `Addr`, `Path`, `StaticDir`, `Transport`, `StateUpdateLane`, `CellSize` for FOI, optional `LogReplicationStats` (or env `GOLEM_LOG_REPLICATION_STATS=1`) for once-per-second replication batching / wire-size diagnostics), `TickFunc` `func(dt float64, s *Server)`, `ContactFunc` `func(contacts []CollisionContact)`, `OnTick` / `OnUpdates` / `OnContact`, `SetRemovalSerializer`, `SetCollisionBackend`, `Run` with fixed timestep. **Entity world API on `Server`:** `CreateEntity(e, owner ...int64) error` (unowned vs `AddOwned` via optional session ID), `DeleteEntity`, `Get`, `Owner`, `SetOwner`, `All`, `Len`, `SnapshotAll`—all delegate to an internal `*registry.Registry` (`reg` field, unexported). `NewServer` always creates an internal `golem/net.Listener` wired to that registry, with `WrapEntityUpdate` as the reliable stream entity message wrapper and a world snapshot closure. Automatic incremental entity replication uses `StateUpdateLaneDatagram` over WebTransport by default; `StateUpdateLaneStream` keeps incremental updates on the reliable stream. Datagram state updates use compact state records for known-entity deltas and fall oversized/full-state payloads back to the reliable stream. When `CellSize > 0`, an `interest.Manager` is created and interest management is enabled (entity snapshots on connect are deferred). When `Addr` is set, `Run` starts both the tick loop and the built-in HTTP server plus the selected transport endpoint (WebTransport by default, WebSocket when configured with `StateUpdateLaneStream`). When `Addr` is empty, `Run` only ticks; the game mounts `Handler()` on its own router or HTTP/3 server.

**Interest management:** when enabled (`CellSize > 0`), `AssignFOI(sessionID, entityID, radius, margin)` and `RemoveFOI(sessionID)` control per-session fields of interest. The tick loop uses `runInterestTick`: update grid positions → compute per-session diffs → flush registry → per-session filtered sends (entered entities get `FullUpdate`, stayed+dirty get delta or compact datagram record, exited get removal). Global entities (`IsGlobal() == true`) always appear in every session's interest set. When interest is **not** enabled, the original `runBroadcastTick` blindly broadcasts all updates to all sessions.

**Collision integration:** opt-in via `SetCollisionBackend(b collision.Backend)`. When a backend is set, each tick runs after `onTick` and before the flush: (1) `backend.Update(id, x, y)` for every live entity, widening float32 entity positions to float64, (2) `backend.Step(dt)` → `[]Contact`, (3) `backend.ReadBack` writes physics-corrected positions back to entities that implement `PositionWriter` (`SetPosition(x, y float32)`), narrowing from float64 at the runtime boundary, (4) `onContact` fires if set and contacts were found (only when `len(contacts) > 0`), (5) `dispatchContactEvents` fires if `contactEventsEnabled` is true — called **unconditionally** (even on zero contacts) so Exit events are detected when all overlaps end. **Shape registration (`backend.Add` / `backend.Remove`) is not wired by the server**—call it in `OnSpawn`/`OnRemove` entity hooks or game logic. **`backend.Set(entityID, shape, layer, mask, trigger)`** replaces an entity's shape, filter, and trigger flag without despawning it; the entity's current position is preserved; no-op if the id is not registered.

**Per-entity collision events:** opt-in via `EnableContactEvents()`, which sets `contactEventsEnabled = true` and allocates `triggerPairs map[[2]int64]struct{}` and `solidPairs map[[2]int64]struct{}` (both fields on `Server`, defined in `loop.go`). Requires a collision backend. Six opt-in entity interfaces in `golem/collision_events.go`: `TriggerEnter`, `TriggerStay`, `TriggerExit` (method arg: `other Entity`); `CollisionEnter`, `CollisionStay`, `CollisionExit` (method args: `other Entity, normal CollisionVec2, depth float64`). `dispatchContactEvents(contacts []collision.Contact)` in `collision_events.go`: splits contacts into `currentTrigger` (Depth==0) and `currentSolid` (Depth>0) maps keyed by `contactKey(a,b int64) [2]int64` (canonical min-first pair); fires Enter/Stay/Exit by comparing current maps against `triggerPairs`/`solidPairs`; swaps the maps at the end. **Normal convention:** `Contact.Normal` is the push direction for `Contact.A` (unit vector from B toward A); entity B receives the negated vector so both sides get a normal pointing away from the other. **nil other:** if `reg.Get` returns false for a partner, `other` is passed as nil; the receiver entity still gets the callback (guarded by its own `okA`/`okB`). Both sides can be stale simultaneously — neither fires. `contactKey` returns `{min(a,b), max(a,b)}`.

Each tick order: **`s.tick++`** → **`OnTickStart(tick)`** → **`drainMessages()`** (OnConnect / OnMessage / OnDisconnect callbacks here) → **`reg.TickAll(dt)`** → `onTick(dt, s)` → collision step (Update → Step → ReadBack → onContact → dispatchContactEvents) → flush + broadcast → **`OnTickEnd(tick, wall)`**. `tick` is a `uint64` field on `Server`, incremented at the top of each tick (1-based, no atomic needed — single goroutine). `Tick() uint64` returns it for use in game logic (sequence numbers, log lines). All hook callbacks run on the tick goroutine, so `runtime/trace` regions and `pprof.Do` labels nest cleanly with work done in `OnTick`.

**Session event queue:** `OnConnect`, `OnMessage`, and `OnDisconnect` are enqueued from connection goroutines (via internal `enqueueConnect` / `enqueueMessage` / `enqueueDisconnect` hooks installed on the `Listener` in `NewServer`) and dispatched on the tick goroutine during `drainMessages`. The user-facing `OnConnect(fn)` / `OnMessage(fn)` / `OnDisconnect(fn)` methods **only store `fn`** — they no longer call `s.listener.On*`. This makes it safe to call `CreateEntity`, `DeleteEntity`, entity `Set*` methods, and all other `Server` APIs from all three callbacks without any additional synchronization. Events are queued in a buffered channel of capacity 4096; if the queue is full the event is dropped and a warning is logged (the connection goroutine is never blocked). Each event fires up to one tick after it occurs — `OnConnect` in particular fires on the tick after the world-state snapshot is delivered, which shifts when the player entity appears relative to the interest system's first visibility pass. `OnUpgrade` is unaffected and still runs synchronously before the WebSocket is accepted.

**External router support:** `Handler()` returns the active transport endpoint handler for mounting on a custom router (e.g. Chi alongside REST routes). `OnUpgrade(func(*http.Request) (any, error))` provides pre-upgrade auth; the returned value populates `Session.Data` before `OnConnect` fires, and a non-nil error rejects with HTTP 401. When using WebTransport on a caller-owned server, pair `Handler()` with `WebTransportServer(...)` on HTTP/3. Session lifecycle hooks: `OnConnect`, `OnMessage`, `OnDisconnect`, and `OnDatagram` for the lossy WebTransport lane. Direct-send helpers: `Send(sessionID, data)`, `Broadcast(data)`, `SendUnreliable(data)` / `BroadcastUnreliable(data)` when the transport supports datagrams.

**`servermsg.go`**: `WrapEntityUpdate` wraps `EntityUpdate` bytes in a `ServerMessage` envelope (proto field 1, length-delimited). `WrapWorldUpdate` wraps `WorldUpdate` bytes in a `ServerMessage` envelope (proto field 2, length-delimited). The `Listener` applies `WrapEntityUpdate` transparently via its `messageWrapper`; world frames bypass it entirely and use `WrapWorldUpdate` via the world snapshot closure or `BroadcastRaw`.

**`export.go`** re-exports `Entity`, opt-in entity interfaces `Ticker`, `Spawner`, `Remover`, `PositionWriter`, `Session` (from `golem/net`), `InterestManager`, `InterestFOI`, `InterestDiff` (from `golem/interest`), `WorldData`/`WorldStore` (from `golem/world`), and collision types `CollisionBackend`, `CollisionContact`, `CollisionShape`, `CollisionCircle`, `CollisionAABB`, `CollisionVec2` (from `golem.collision`) so consumers use a single **`golem`** import path. Six per-entity collision event interfaces (`TriggerEnter`, `TriggerStay`, `TriggerExit`, `CollisionEnter`, `CollisionStay`, `CollisionExit`) are defined directly in `golem/collision_events.go` — also in the `golem` package, no re-export aliases needed. **`Registry` / `FlushResult` / `NewRegistry` are not re-exported**—use `golem.Server` for gameplay or import `golem/registry` for low-level embedding.

**World data** (`Server.World`): `*world.Store` is always initialized. `Server.PushWorldData(name) error` broadcasts one world type to all sessions; returns nil when the name is missing or networking is inactive, and returns a non-nil error if `MarshalUpdate` fails. On connect, the listener sends all world data before entity snapshots.

**`golem/world`** package: `Data` interface (`WorldName`, `MarshalUpdate`), thread-safe `Store` (`Set`, `Get`, `MarshalAll` in sorted name order). No dependencies on `golem`, `golem/net`, or `golem/registry`.

Depends on **`golem/registry`** for entity storage, **`golem/net`** for networking, **`golem/interest`** for FOI management, **`golem/world`** for world data, and **`golem.collision`** (local sibling module, resolved by `go.work`) for the collision backend interface; does **not** implement `Entity` or registry internals—those stay in `golem/registry/`.

**`golem/debug`** subpackage: `StartPprof(addr string) error` starts a pprof HTTP debug server on `addr` (e.g. `"127.0.0.1:6060"`). Uses a dedicated `http.ServeMux` — `http.DefaultServeMux` is not touched. All pprof handlers (`/debug/pprof/`, `/cmdline`, `/profile`, `/symbol`, `/trace`) are mounted explicitly via the named `net/http/pprof` import. Since the import lives only in `golem/debug`, production binaries that do not import it never register pprof handlers. Call from `main` behind a flag; never import in production builds.
